#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 trunk5 stable5
#: commands.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "The paste operation in &kxstitch; allows you to press and hold the &LMB; down roughly in the position that the paste data is to go which will provide an image of the paste data to allow accurate positioning before releasing the mouse button to finalize the position. This technique is also used for the mirroring and rotate functions. The cursor keys can also be used to move the pasted pattern around and the &Enter; key used to fix the position."
msgstr ""

